  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\n\r\nFrom our October 4 standup discussion, it makes sense for Lodestar to also consume the light client p2p data it produces from its full node (#4365). The beneficial use cases of such an application is to open the doors to other clients and developers to consume light client data for their use case (e.g. A light client CL to get latest blocks for an execution client). We must streamline the development of a standalone light client data consumer which inherits the pieces from light client p2p. \r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n\r\nGoal: We should develop a lightweight, standalone consumer inheriting light client data from the p2p network. Some additional points to note:\r\n- It should be a separate process so others may bundle this with their application\r\n- It must listen to gossip and get updates from req/res (the challenge with our current libs/modules is getting it to work outside of the beacon node without breaking Lodestar and is safe)\r\n- It will have to use a defined list of bootnodes or discv5 to discover nodes through p2p \r\n\r\n**To Investigate/Research**\r\n- Lodestar can have an advantage for browsers. Can we add a websocket transport for publishing?\r\n\r\n**Ideas + Roadmap for Implementation (subject to change)**\r\nMilestone 1: Replicate something similar to our browser demo without going through P2P\r\nMilestone 2: Interop with Nimbus light client via P2P",
