    "body": "A websocket transport for publishing is interesting, a simple way to request data from ABIs of contracts maybe, I think the most useful features has to be to be enabled with Ethers and Web3Js via Http or Ipc, there is also new libraries built with web3py that use Http in a promising way, https://web3js.readthedocs.io/en/v1.2.1/getting-started.html, https://docs.ethers.io/v5/getting-started/#getting-started--connecting-rpc, a lot of dApps are already built on these standards and consuming data from Infura or Alchemy, \r\nThis availability of data request creates a easy way to gather blockchain data without needing full nodes,\r\nThe feature of verifying NFT balances is something used for many dApps, \r\nI am surprised that this client for beacon api seems to be abandoned; \r\nhttps://github.com/web3j/web3j-eth2\r\n\r\nIt is hard to understand how the merge is a technological upgrade, but now a barrier to enabling light nodes,\r\n\r\n\r\n",
